Da Gama was then asked directly whether he’d be interested in taking over the hotseat, to which he replied by providing reasons why he’s suited to the role. 
 
“It would be an honour to be Bafana coach one day, I think any coach in South Africa would be interested,” he continued. “There’s that natural progression, so why not? I’ve got the experience and I’ve coach at the highest level in the PSL, I’ve played at the highest level in Europe, and we’ve got immediate knowledge of the team, so why not? I’ve got a lot of confidence in myself and my ability, but I will wait for my bosses at SAFA, however, to give me directions.”</TEXT> 
